<!-- ==========================================================
(User Registration Page)

Description:
Template for user registration. Allows new users to create
an account using email/password or Google sign-in.

Responsibilities:
- Render registration form with nickname, email, and password.
- Provide alternative registration via Google OAuth.
- Include navigation to login page for existing users.
- Support internationalization (i18n) for all labels and buttons.

Structure:
- Includes global header and footer partials.
- Organized using BEM CSS naming convention.
- Divided into:
  1. Registration form section
  2. Alternative login/Google options section

Client-Side Behavior:
- Form submission handled by register.js
- Validates nickname, email, and password fields.
- Prevents double submission.
- Provides feedback via SweetAlert2 modals.
- Supports logout after registration to prevent auto-login session.

Dependencies:
- register.js
- auth.js (Firebase or backend integration)
- Google OAuth scripts (if used)
- i18n system
- Global bundle.min.js

Security Notes:
- Password field uses type="password".
- Required HTML attributes ensure basic client validation.
- Nickname and email validated before submission.
- Sensitive operations handled in JavaScript/backend; no password stored in template.

========================================================== -->

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="register">
  <h1 class="register__titulo" data-i18n="registerTitle"></h1>

  <form id="register-form" class="register__form">

    <label for="" class="register__form--nickname" data-i18n="nickname"></label>
    <input id="register-nick" class="register__form--input" type="text" required />

    <label class="register__form--tituloEmail" data-i18n="emailRegister"></label>
    <input id="register-email" class="register__form--input" type="email" required />

    <label class="register__form--passw" data-i18n="passwordRegister"></label>
    <input id="register-pass" class="register__form--input" type="password" required />

    <button class="register__form--submit" type="submit" data-i18n="submitRegister"></button>
  </form>

  <div class="register__options">
    <button id="google-btn" class="register__options--google" data-i18n="googleCreate"></button>
    <a class="register__options--cuenta" href="/login" data-i18n="createExist"></a>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>